==English==

===Etymology===
Latin, ''status'', [[state]] and suffix [[ist]]. Probably originated from Italian or other Romance language, ''statista'' in the 17th. century. 

===Noun===
# A supporter of [[statism]]
# A statistician. (not common)
# A skilled politician or one with political power, knowledge or influence. (outdated, common in 17th century) 

===Adjective===
Relating to [[statism]].